>nmm@cl.cam.ac.uk writes:

>>In article <1993Oct2.124024.24965@uwasa.fi> hensel@garbo.uwasa.fi (Mike Hensel)
>>writes:
>>>i intend to develop a program for ms-dos that will encrypt hard disks
>>>on a sector level. for this, i need a fast and strong cipher, that
[part deleted]

>Big problem: if user runs a disk defragmentation program, which
>moves data among sectors as necessary in order to ensure contiguous
>storage. Then secondary keys may no longer match up with encrypted data.
>In this case you have to supply your own defrag program, and
>make sure user uses only that one.

If you encrypt on the sector level, the FAT etc should be encrypted too.

Then any defragmentation program should work except those that do
not access the disk through the bios.

